headline: How Investors May Respond To Moderna (MRNA) Halting Development of mRNA-1647 CMV Vaccine
summary: Moderna announced in October 2025 that it will discontinue development of its investigational cytomegalovirus (CMV) vaccine, mRNA-1647, following disappointing results from a Phase 3 clinical trial that did not meet its primary efficacy endpoint in seronegative women of childbearing age. This decision marks a setback for one of Moderna’s most advanced late-stage programs, highlighting the ongoing risks and volatility inherent in late-stage vaccine development.
